Dairy Farm International Holdings Ltd. said in Hong Kong first-half after-tax profit rose 26% to 383 million Hong Kong dollars (US$49 million) from a year earlier, while net income after preference dividends jumped 32% to HK$332 million from HK$252 million the previous year. 

The food and retail group's per-share earnings rose 25% to 24.3 cents from 19.4 cents and turnover increased 20% to HK$9.20 billion from HK$7.64 billion a year earlier. 

Dairy Farm Chairman Simon Keswick said business among its supermarkets, drugstores, fast-food chains and newly acquired 7-Eleven convenience stores during the period was generally good. 

